title: 1896 Cork Senior Football Championship
text:
The 1896 Cork Senior Football Championship was the 10th staging of the <a href="Cork%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">Cork Senior Football Championship</a> since its establishment by the <a href="Cork%20GAA">Cork County Board</a> in <a href="1887%20Cork%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">1887</a>.
<a href="Fermoy%20GAA">Fermoy</a> were the <a href="1895%20Cork%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">defending champions</a>.
<a href="Lees%20GAA">Lees</a> won the championship following a 0-03 to 0-00 defeat of <a href="Kanturk%20GAA">Kanturk</a> in the final at Cork Park. This was their third title overall and their first title since <a href="1888%20Cork%20Senior%20Football%20Championship">1888</a>.
